---
globs: *.tsx,*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---
- Use named exports instead of default exports for components
- Keep components focused and appropriately sized
- Use constants from constants directory instead of hardcoded strings
- Use TypeScript interfaces for component props and state
- Handle loading and error states in components
- Use custom hooks for complex logic and side effects
- Pass onSuccess/onError callbacks to React Query hooks instead of using useEffect to handle success/error states
- Never use `any` type - always use proper TypeScript types
- Follow React best practices for performance optimization
- Always use react query/mutation instead of the fetch
